<br>
First I must say that I used this plan to go from 20-175 for about 1kpp. Thats with a Wis of 163, Str of 95, and Chr of 101. Your milage may vary. Also I tended to sell back to vendors as much as possible and wasted no time trying to sell to players. I also was based in Freeport at the time. Never stack any items in forge, and only use real water, not summoned or foraged.<br>
<br>
Step 1. Drop 20 points into smithing skill at your guild.<br>
<br>
Step 2. Metal Bits (triv at 21).<br>
      Recipe = (2) small PIECES of ore , one water <br>
<br>
     Buy ore from Kyrin at Groflah's Forge, NFP<br>
<br>
    Ok this is the nasty step as you will use 400-500 metal bits making items down the road. I tended to make one backpack full, then went on to step 3, this improved my skill so when I needed more bits, I failed on the combine less. In each step as I ran out of bits, I went back to step two and make another backpack full.<br>
<br>
Step 3. Make Scalers to 41<br>
      Recipe = one metal bits, one scaler mold, one water<br>
<br>
      Buy scaler mold from Tristan at Traders Holiday, EFP<br>
<br>
Step 4. Make Toolboxes to 51<br>
      Recipe = one metal bits, water<br>
<br>
Step 5. Make Lanterns to 68<br>
      Recipe = one metal bits, lantern casing mold,  one empty bottle, one water<br>
       <br>
      buy lantern casing mold from Trislan at Traders Holiday, EFP<br>
      buy empty bottles numerous places, I got them from the Hogcaller's Inn over by the Militia House in  WFP.<br>
<br>
Step 6. Make Skewers to 115<br>
     Recipe = one metal bits, one skewer mold, one water<br>
<br>
     buy skewer mold  from Trislan at Traders Holiday, EFP<br>
<br>
Step 7. Make Pots to 122<br>
     Recipe = one metal bits, one pot mold, one standing legs mold, one water<br>
<br>
     buy pot and standing legs molds from Trislan at Traders Holiday, EFP<br>
<br>
<br>
Step 8. Make Sewing Kits to 135<br>
      Recipe = one metal bits, one needle mold, one thimble mold, one water.<br>
<br>
      buy needle and thimble molds from Jilian at Vilithe &amp; Bardo's, EFP ( I think, will check and edit here)<br>
<br>
Step 9. Make Banded Mantles to 168<br>
      Recipe = (2) metal sheets, one mantle mold, one water<br>
<br>
      buy metal sheets and banded molds from Issilyn at Armor by Ithkar, EFP<br>
<br>
Step 10. Make Banded Cloaks to 175<br>
      Recipe = (2) metal sheets, one cloak mold, one water<br>
<br>
      buy metal sheets and banded molds from Issilyn at Armor by Ithkar, EFP<br>
<br>
You have now triviled all Banded Armor and are ready to start into Fine Steel Plate Armor, which I will post about at a later time. Any questions or comments please feel free to post or send tell.<br>
